1
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:51,800
Whether it's spirits like you
or living humans...

2
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:53,399
...it spares no one.

3
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,720
What do you mean?

4
00:02:55,720 --> 00:02:57,640
What's that light?

5
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:08,760
Get off this island!

6
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:12,840
Is someone out there?
Please open the door.

7
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,199
What are you going to do now?

8
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:17,760
Go check out
the shallow-water coral around here.

9
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:25,480
Calm down.

10
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,760
Are you okay?

11
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:31,080
Did you get a cramp?

12
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:37,560
Luckily, I turned around and saw you.

13
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:41,560
But why did you sink so fast?

14
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:44,200
You scared me to death.

15
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,120
I didn't get a cramp.

16
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:54,040
Mook, something dragged my leg underwater.

17
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:57,359
What?

18
00:04:57,360 --> 00:05:00,159
Mook, it was terrifying.

19
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:02,240
Really terrifying.

20
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,480
It's okay.

21
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:08,080
It's me.

22
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:13,240
Dad.

23
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:17,320
Why are you still here?
Why won't you listen to me?

24
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,599
I can't leave yet.

25
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:21,640
Why not?

26
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:24,479
Mr. Narathon and Kaimook once helped me.

27
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:28,320
Now they're on this island.
I'm trying to get them to leave.

28
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:31,920
Dad, the thing on this island...

29
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:36,919
Dad!

30
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,480
What's wrong?!

31
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:41,440
Dad!

32
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,120
Go.

33
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:48,119
Go now. Get everyone out of here.

34
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,839
- Go now!
- No.

35
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:51,879
Dad, what's happening to you?

36
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:53,000
Dad!

37
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:56,520
Dad!

38
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:14,600
So the thing dragging your leg underwater
was a ghost?

39
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:18,040
Yes. This island is haunted.

40
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:21,679
I've felt something strange
ever since I arrived.

41
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:22,840
I just wasn't sure before.

42
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:26,200
Da has a sixth sense.

43
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:28,320
Sixth sense?

44
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:30,920
It's true, Professor.

45
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:40,959
I want to go home.
I don't want to stay here another minute.

46
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:44,919
Da, listen to me.
We didn't come here on vacation.

47
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,159
We came here to work.

48
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:48,680
And we haven't gotten
any actual results yet.

49
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:52,439
Professor's right.

50
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,800
The two of us are here
for an internship, remember?

51
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:27,280
Just endure it for two more days.

52
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,640
Do what Mr. Narathon said.

53
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:34,080
He already shortened
the internship schedule a lot.

54
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:39,240
Mr. Narathon's trying his best to help us.

55
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,480
I can't shake this bad feeling.

56
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:53,479
If you're uncomfortable,
then don't dive again.

57
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:57,480
I, Mr. Narathon and the professor
will handle it ourselves.

58
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:01,880
I don't think I have a choice.

59
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,599
Wait, Da.

60
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,719
You were wearing a sacred thread bracelet.

61
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:11,080
How could a ghost still attack you?

62
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,360
Oh?

63
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:23,680
I don't even know when I lost it.

64
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,400
No wonder...

65
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:29,040
Mook, don't leave me.

66
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:33,000
I won't leave you.

67
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:36,639
Nothing's going to happen. Get some rest.

68
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:38,480
I'll stay here with you.

69
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:45,720
Don't go anywhere while I'm asleep, okay?

70
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,160
Okay.

71
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:50,240
Just sleep.

72
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:02,680
Mr. Narathon?

73
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:06,240
Why were you standing there so quietly?

74
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:10,200
I was checking around.

75
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:13,600
Where are you going at this time?

76
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,279
I'm going to get some water.

77
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:17,640
I forgot to bring any back
earlier tonight.

78
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:19,840
I'll go with you.

79
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:22,160
Thank you.

80
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:24,000
Please.

81
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:44,560
Is something wrong?

82
00:11:47,920 --> 00:11:49,000
Nothing.

83
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:42,600
Excuse me. The gallery isn't open
to the public yet. How did you get in?

84
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:48,639
Sorry. I saw the door wasn't locked.

85
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:51,679
I love beautiful underwater photography,

86
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:53,279
so I came in to take a look.

87
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:54,800
I'm sorry.

88
00:12:55,920 --> 00:12:58,999
Those movers
must've forgotten to lock the door.

89
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,640
Careless idiots.

90
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:04,200
Are you the owner of this gallery?

91
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,440
Yes. I'm Phum Witassanai.

92
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:08,039
Oh.

93
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:11,640
One of Thailand's most successful
real estate businessmen.

94
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:16,240
I never imagined
you'd be this young and handsome.

95
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:19,799
But I still don't know your name.

96
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:23,560
I'm Pat.
I live in your condominium, actually.

97
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:26,240
So we're neighbors.

98
00:13:26,920 --> 00:13:28,400
Nice to meet you.

99
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:30,120
Likewise.

100
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:34,360
By the way,

101
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:39,400
where was this Black Coral photographed?

102
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:44,160
I forgot to ask the photographer
when I bought it.

103
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:47,079
There are many more interesting pieces.

104
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:51,000
You should come
on the official opening day.

105
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:52,879
Sure.

106
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:54,560
I definitely will.

107
00:14:09,560 --> 00:14:10,400
Pat.

108
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:13,160
Pawin.

109
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,440
What do you want?

110
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:17,840
The moment I'm no longer useful,

111
00:14:18,680 --> 00:14:20,800
you look at me like you've seen a ghost.

112
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:24,960
If you came here
just to start a fight, then leave.

113
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:27,760
Pat.

114
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:29,240
Pat,

115
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:31,680
I miss you.

116
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:34,000
Let's get back together.

117
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:36,840
Pawin.

118
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,960
Did you misunderstand something?

119
00:14:41,920 --> 00:14:45,399
I only was with you because of work.

120
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:47,480
Once the job was done,

121
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:51,000
everything ended. That's normal.

122
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:55,080
Pat.

123
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:58,919
Easy for you to say.
But I'm not ending this so easily.

124
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:00,599
- That hurts.
- I love you.

125
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:02,399
Do you hear me? I love you.

126
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:03,919
- That hurts. Let go of me.
- I won't.

127
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:05,319
- Let go of me now.
- I love you.

128
00:15:05,320 --> 00:15:06,360
Let Ms. Pat go right now.

129
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:09,360
Mr. Phum.

130
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:14,080
If you don't let her go,
I'll have security throw you out.

131
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:19,599
Who are you? Stay out of this.

132
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:21,920
I'm the owner of this condominium.

133
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:25,120
Would you like
to be charged with trespassing?

134
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:30,320
Mr. Phum.

135
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:34,760
Is there a problem, sir?

136
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:49,639
Keep a closer watch
on who comes in and out.

137
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:52,119
If they're not residents,
don't let them in under any circumstances.

138
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:53,679
Good thing
he didn't make it inside the building.

139
00:15:53,680 --> 00:15:54,880
Yes, sir.

140
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:57,519
But that man

141
00:15:57,520 --> 00:15:59,599
used to come here often with this lady,

142
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:01,199
so I thought they were dating.

143
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,560
That's why I let him in.

144
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:10,400
If you and your boyfriend ever make up,
please apologize to him for me.

145
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:21,800
Damn you, Pawin.

146
00:16:22,560 --> 00:16:24,040
You ruined my plan.

147
00:16:24,560 --> 00:16:25,600
Idiot.

148
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:33,360
Thank you for accompanying me.

149
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:36,560
No problem.

150
00:16:38,280 --> 00:16:41,320
How's Ms. Dara doing?

151
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:43,919
She's fast asleep.

152
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:47,320
She's probably exhausted and scared.

153
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:51,200
What about you? Are you scared?

154
00:16:52,640 --> 00:16:56,359
No. Why would I be scared
when there's such a kind

155
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:57,760
night watchman looking after me?

156
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:01,600
I just wasn't sleepy yet.

157
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:05,959
Don't forget we're photographing
underwater tomorrow.

158
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:08,440
You should get enough rest.

159
00:17:13,599 --> 00:17:15,920
Thank you for worrying about me.

160
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:19,960
I should be the one thanking you.

161
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:24,640
Let's go.

162
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:26,680
I'll walk you to your room.

163
00:17:57,280 --> 00:17:59,920
If you hate me so much that
you can't even stand looking at me,

164
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:02,040
then why did you marry me?

165
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:06,799
I'm tired. Let me shower first.

166
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,360
Stop picking a fight.

167
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:11,040
I'm not picking a fight.

168
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:12,880
I just want to know.

169
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:17,160
Please, Sairung.
I'm really exhausted today.

170
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:25,800
Mr. Phum, what is this?

171
00:18:26,760 --> 00:18:29,000
What's wrong with you?

172
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:35,079
Of course you're tired. You've been
fooling around with someone all day.

173
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:36,519
That's too much.

174
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:37,840
It's not even enough.

175
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:41,639
I actually thought the reason
you ignored me

176
00:18:41,640 --> 00:18:44,079
and never touched me
after Sarai disappeared

177
00:18:44,080 --> 00:18:45,679
- was because...
- Hey!

178
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:46,800
Stop!

179
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:50,559
How many times have I told you
never say that name again.

180
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:51,560
I don't want to hear it!

181
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:24,840
Is it morning already?

182
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:28,400
No, it's only 2 a.m.

183
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:34,720
Then why are you awake?

184
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:37,840
I couldn't sleep.

185
00:19:42,560 --> 00:19:44,040
Is something wrong?

186
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:48,440
Nothing happened.

187
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:51,040
I just went to check
that everything was alright.

188
00:19:56,480 --> 00:19:57,920
You're worried about Kaimook, aren't you?

189
00:20:01,320 --> 00:20:02,280
What did you say?

190
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:05,480
If someone hears you,
they'll misunderstand.

191
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:08,840
Go to sleep.

192
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,360
Misunderstand what?

193
00:20:12,440 --> 00:20:14,160
I think I understand perfectly.

194
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:19,040
Stop making that sound.

195
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:58,520
Kaimook, are you in the bathroom?

196
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:04,680
Mook.

197
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:18,360
I knew it.
You're not a real friend after all.

198
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:29,280
Ms. Dara, are you feeling better?

199
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:31,880
Yes.

200
00:22:34,600 --> 00:22:36,040
Where's Kaimook?

201
00:22:37,040 --> 00:22:38,079
Oh?

202
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:39,559
She's not in the room.

203
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:42,640
I'm still mad at her
for leaving without waiting for me.

204
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:48,280
Has anyone seen Kaimook this morning?

205
00:22:48,920 --> 00:22:53,520
Well, I woke up at six
to prepare breakfast,

206
00:22:54,120 --> 00:22:57,480
and I still didn't see
Ms. Kaimook come out of her room.

207
00:22:58,080 --> 00:22:59,600
We didn't see her either.

208
00:23:04,680 --> 00:23:06,040
Then,

209
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:08,920
let's split up and search for Kaimook.

210
00:23:10,280 --> 00:23:12,000
- Yes.
- Let's go.

211
00:23:17,360 --> 00:23:18,280
Kaimook!

212
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:26,440
Kaimook!

213
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:28,520
Kaimook!

214
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:32,600
Mook!

215
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:46,760
- Ms. Kaimook.
- Ms. Kaimook.

216
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:49,560
Ms. Kaimook.

217
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:52,599
Did you find her?

218
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:54,080
No, ma'am.

219
00:23:58,880 --> 00:23:59,799
Did you find her?

220
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:02,720
- No.
- No, I searched the whole island.

221
00:24:03,960 --> 00:24:05,480
- Did you find her?
- No.

222
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:14,120
Or maybe Mook disappeared because of...

223
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:15,920
Of...

224
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:20,320
A ghost?

225
00:25:06,560 --> 00:25:09,600
Or Kaimook really did leave the room.

226
00:25:10,240 --> 00:25:11,120
Hm?

227
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:13,040
Where could she go?

228
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:43,600
The footprints disappear here.

229
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:13,960
Ms. Da.

230
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:18,800
What's wrong?

231
00:26:22,200 --> 00:26:23,280
Ms. Dara?

232
00:26:30,320 --> 00:26:31,440
Mr. Thon,

233
00:26:32,120 --> 00:26:34,599
Mook really was taken away.
It was terrifying.

234
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:36,560
That thing definitely wasn't human.

235
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:44,040
Ms. Dara, then where did it take Kaimook?

236
00:26:46,840 --> 00:26:47,840
I...

237
00:26:50,040 --> 00:26:51,520
I couldn't see.

238
00:27:07,680 --> 00:27:10,639
Ms. Da, what's wrong?

239
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:13,159
What's happened?

240
00:27:13,160 --> 00:27:16,199
The ghost. That woman ghost.

241
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:17,520
Oh my.

242
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:20,120
Where? I couldn't see anything.

243
00:27:33,680 --> 00:27:35,480
She's over there.

244
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:54,440
There's nothing.

245
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,320
Ms. Da,

246
00:28:09,320 --> 00:28:10,360
what is it?

247
00:28:14,040 --> 00:28:15,400
It's like...

248
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:18,920
she wants us to follow her.

249
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:22,920
Or maybe

250
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:26,040
she knows where Kaimook is.

251
00:28:27,160 --> 00:28:29,400
Ms. Da, we have to follow her.

252
00:28:31,960 --> 00:28:34,119
No, I'm scared.

253
00:28:34,120 --> 00:28:35,600
Ms. Da,

254
00:28:36,240 --> 00:28:38,560
you're the only one who can see her.

255
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:41,039
We need to follow her.

256
00:28:41,040 --> 00:28:42,920
I believe she won't hurt us.

257
00:28:43,720 --> 00:28:46,360
We need to follow her.

258
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:49,200
I'm going with you.

259
00:28:49,960 --> 00:28:52,360
I won't leave you, I promise.

260
00:28:53,600 --> 00:28:57,040
Are you really going to follow a ghost?

261
00:28:57,720 --> 00:29:00,720
If you want to go, then go. I'm not going.

262
00:29:02,400 --> 00:29:04,600
- Okay. Then you stay here.
- Okay.

263
00:29:05,680 --> 00:29:06,720
Let's go.

264
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:14,519
<i>The number you have dialed
cannot be connected at the moment.</i>

265
00:29:14,520 --> 00:29:15,440
<i>The number you have dialed cannot be--</i>

266
00:29:19,040 --> 00:29:19,999
<i>The number you have dialed</i>

267
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,119
- <i>cannot be connected at the moment.</i>
- Dear.

268
00:29:21,120 --> 00:29:22,600
- Your lemongrass tea.
- <i>The number you have dialed</i>

269
00:29:23,120 --> 00:29:24,399
<i>cannot be connected at the moment.</i>

270
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:27,959
Drink it while it's warm.
It helps with all sorts of pains,

271
00:29:27,960 --> 00:29:29,200
especially sore legs.

272
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:35,080
I have a bad feeling
something's happened to Kaimook.

273
00:29:35,600 --> 00:29:37,040
I can't reach her at all.

274
00:29:37,640 --> 00:29:39,359
Oh come on, dear.

275
00:29:39,360 --> 00:29:41,880
I think you're overthinking this.

276
00:29:44,200 --> 00:29:45,360
Where are you going?

277
00:29:46,480 --> 00:29:47,800
I'm going to Save Sea.

278
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:49,799
I'm coming too.

279
00:29:49,800 --> 00:29:51,000
Wait.

280
00:30:10,480 --> 00:30:14,040
Dara, we're heading
toward the back of the island now.

281
00:30:14,640 --> 00:30:17,280
Can you still see that woman ghost?

282
00:30:23,800 --> 00:30:24,680
Yes.

283
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:27,040
She keeps appearing for me
from time to time.

284
00:30:30,040 --> 00:30:32,080
She's over there now.

285
00:30:36,520 --> 00:30:40,039
Let's keep following her.
I'm sure she's leading us to Kaimook.

286
00:30:40,040 --> 00:30:40,960
Let's go.

287
00:30:54,080 --> 00:30:57,000
Please contact Mr. Narathon
at the research center on Skull Island.

288
00:30:57,600 --> 00:30:59,400
Once you reach him,
transfer the call to me immediately.

289
00:31:03,480 --> 00:31:05,839
I'm really sorry for troubling you,

290
00:31:05,840 --> 00:31:08,799
but you know, we're parents.

291
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:10,519
When your child
suddenly goes completely silent like this,

292
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:12,399
you can't help but worry.

293
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:15,120
It's alright. I understand.

294
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:16,960
Alright.

295
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:22,840
Yes?

296
00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:28,440
Okay, okay.

297
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:37,760
We can't reach anyone on the island now.

298
00:32:18,320 --> 00:32:19,320
What is it?

299
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:24,480
That woman ghost
has been gone for a while now.

300
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:27,400
I don't know why she stopped appearing.

301
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:31,000
Then where should we go now?

302
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:37,560
Or maybe Kaimook is somewhere around here.

303
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:41,360
If that's the case,
let's search this area first.

304
00:32:43,160 --> 00:32:46,119
Kaimook. Kaimook.

305
00:32:46,120 --> 00:32:47,919
- Kaimook.
- Kaimook.

306
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:49,839
- Kaimook.
- Mook.

307
00:32:49,840 --> 00:32:52,159
- Kaimook.
- Do you hear me, Mook?

308
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:53,240
Kaimook.

309
00:32:54,040 --> 00:32:55,080
Mook.

310
00:35:11,480 --> 00:35:12,560
Kaimook.

311
00:35:15,360 --> 00:35:18,320
- Mook.
- Kaimook.

312
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:22,000
- Kaimook.
- Mook.

313
00:35:23,320 --> 00:35:24,520
Mook.

314
00:35:48,160 --> 00:35:49,680
What's happening?

315
00:36:18,440 --> 00:36:21,800
What are those holes?
They look like graves.

316
00:36:32,360 --> 00:36:34,319
Ghosts are crawling out of the graves!

317
00:36:34,320 --> 00:36:36,639
Where are they?

318
00:36:36,640 --> 00:36:38,439
- They're crawling out!
- Stay calm.

319
00:36:38,440 --> 00:36:40,359
Don't split up.

320
00:36:40,360 --> 00:36:42,319
Think carefully,
there has to be a way to fight them.

321
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:43,679
Fight ghosts?

322
00:36:43,680 --> 00:36:44,960
Go!

323
00:36:45,760 --> 00:36:46,960
Go!

324
00:36:47,560 --> 00:36:49,760
What do we do? They're coming.

325
00:37:09,320 --> 00:37:10,480
What happened?

326
00:37:11,640 --> 00:37:12,840
What happened?

327
00:37:13,360 --> 00:37:15,120
Another ghost came and saved us.

328
00:37:19,560 --> 00:37:20,480
Go back.

329
00:37:30,680 --> 00:37:31,960
The ghosts are gone now.

330
00:37:36,120 --> 00:37:39,279
He told us to go back. It was terrifying.

331
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:40,199
- Let's go back.
- No.

332
00:37:40,200 --> 00:37:41,480
I'm not going back.

333
00:37:42,320 --> 00:37:45,840
I need to find Kaimook.
She must be in danger.

334
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:35,320
Am I on a ship?

335
00:38:57,920 --> 00:38:59,280
Mr. Narathon.

336
00:39:02,600 --> 00:39:04,040
Mr. Narathon.

337
00:39:24,800 --> 00:39:26,600
Why are you here?

338
00:39:51,040 --> 00:39:52,800
Is someone out there?

339
00:39:53,680 --> 00:39:56,640
Is someone out there?
Please open the door for me.

340
00:39:58,200 --> 00:40:01,520
Is someone out there?
Please open the door for me.

341
00:40:13,240 --> 00:40:15,559
Here are your shirts.

342
00:40:15,560 --> 00:40:16,999
Thank you.

343
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:19,000
What are you two doing?

344
00:40:20,120 --> 00:40:22,800
Whoa, where are you guys off to?

345
00:40:23,920 --> 00:40:25,760
Perfect timing.

346
00:40:26,680 --> 00:40:28,400
Have you heard of Skull Island?

347
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:32,000
I've heard of it.

348
00:40:32,520 --> 00:40:35,159
Sailors say it's a cursed island.

349
00:40:35,160 --> 00:40:37,920
Unless absolutely necessary,
people usually avoid that route.

350
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:39,720
Why are you asking?

351
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:44,280
Your sister's on that island.
And right now, we can't contact her.

352
00:40:45,440 --> 00:40:46,720
Take me there.

353
00:40:48,160 --> 00:40:49,000
Alright.

354
00:40:54,640 --> 00:40:55,680
Kaimook.

355
00:40:58,680 --> 00:40:59,600
Mook.

356
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:01,560
Kaimook.

357
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:05,600
- Kaimook.
- Mook, do you hear me?

358
00:41:08,760 --> 00:41:10,120
Kaimook.

359
00:41:12,640 --> 00:41:13,720
Kaimook.

360
00:41:24,800 --> 00:41:27,879
We've searched all the way
to the back of the island already.

361
00:41:27,880 --> 00:41:29,920
There's still no sign of Kaimook.

362
00:41:33,720 --> 00:41:35,600
Let's search around here one more time.

363
00:41:39,040 --> 00:41:40,040
Kaimook!

364
00:41:48,200 --> 00:41:49,800
Can anyone hear me?

365
00:42:24,960 --> 00:42:26,080
Kaimook!

366
00:42:27,320 --> 00:42:28,440
Kaimook!

367
00:42:29,440 --> 00:42:31,160
Mr. Narathon?

368
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:38,480
Mr. Narathon!

369
00:42:39,080 --> 00:42:41,400
Mr. Narathon, I'm in here.

370
00:42:42,320 --> 00:42:43,720
Mr. Narathon.

371
00:42:44,880 --> 00:42:46,999
Mr. Narathon, can you hear me?

372
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:48,600
I'm in here.

373
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:50,640
Mook, can you hear me?

374
00:42:52,680 --> 00:42:53,680
Da!

375
00:42:54,280 --> 00:42:57,000
Da, I'm here. Da.

376
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:01,440
Da. Mr. Narathon.

377
00:43:02,400 --> 00:43:05,199
Mr. Narathon, can you hear me?

378
00:43:05,200 --> 00:43:06,280
I'm inside this ship!

379
00:43:09,560 --> 00:43:11,320
Mr. Narathon.

380
00:43:14,160 --> 00:43:15,440
Did you find her?

381
00:43:16,240 --> 00:43:18,360
There's no sign of Kaimook.

382
00:43:19,160 --> 00:43:22,439
Right. I've shouted so much
my throat hurts already.

383
00:43:22,440 --> 00:43:23,600
Yeah.

384
00:43:24,320 --> 00:43:26,959
I think we should go back
and contact rescue services.

385
00:43:26,960 --> 00:43:28,440
They should send officers
to help search for her.

386
00:43:30,920 --> 00:43:33,120
The professor's right, Mr. Thon.

387
00:43:37,880 --> 00:43:38,720
Let's go.

388
00:43:43,000 --> 00:43:48,240
Don't go yet. Mr. Narathon, I'm in here.

389
00:44:23,560 --> 00:44:25,400
What's happening?

390
00:44:54,120 --> 00:44:56,720
Don't go! Don't go!

391
00:44:59,120 --> 00:45:01,960
- Dear.
- Dad.

392
00:45:07,240 --> 00:45:10,120
You're going to stay here with me forever.

393
00:45:14,280 --> 00:45:16,439
This is bad! This is really bad!

394
00:45:16,440 --> 00:45:18,640
The island!
The boat's gonna crash into the island!

395
00:45:55,040 --> 00:45:56,080
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
